rmed both society’s understanding of the hazards posed by complex technologies and what it takes to make them safe enough.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aNuclear power plantsxRisk assessmentzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aNuclear power plantszUnited StatesxSafety measures. 7aHISTORY / United States / 21st Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520381162zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520381162423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520381162/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles